This product builds upon and references work from the following projects.
None of their source code is forked or modified; they are referenced as
runtime dependencies, recommended companions, or attributed lifts.

============================================================================
gentle-ai
https://github.com/Gentleman-Programming/gentle-ai
============================================================================

Used as a runtime ecosystem dependency. praxis-ai detects gentle-ai's
presence and integrates as an additive overlay. No source code from
gentle-ai is copied, forked, or modified. praxis-ai's overlay is
implemented entirely via Claude Code's @-import directive and HTML
markers in CLAUDE.md, mirroring gentle-ai's own marker convention.

============================================================================
mattpocock/skills
https://github.com/mattpocock/skills
MIT License
============================================================================

Six specific skill files are lifted with attribution:
  - grill-with-docs
  - caveman
  - diagnose
  - zoom-out
  - handoff
  - prototype

Each lifted skill ships with a per-skill NOTICE.md inside its directory
under ~/.claude/skills/<skill-name>/. The NOTICE.md records:
  - MIT License notice
  - Upstream commit SHA
  - Link to original source
  - Statement of modifications (frontmatter additions, body rewrites
    as mechanism rather than ideology)

The bodies of the lifted skills are restructured to be procedural rather
than philosophical, to prevent contradiction with gentle-ai's autonomous
orchestrator instructions when both are loaded in context. The procedural
content remains faithful to the original intent.

============================================================================
RTK (Rust Token Killer)
https://github.com/rtk-ai/rtk
Apache-2.0 License
============================================================================

Recommended as orthogonal tooling for shell-output compression. Not
bundled with praxis-ai. praxis-ai detects RTK's presence and adds a
project-local RTK.md template when initializing a project.

